1626bool llvm::salvageDebugInfo(Instruction &I) {
1627 SmallVector<DbgVariableIntrinsic *, 1> DbgUsers;
1628 findDbgUsers(DbgUsers, &I);
1629 if (DbgUsers.empty())
1630 return false;
1631
1632 return salvageDebugInfoForDbgValues(I, DbgUsers);
1633}
1634
1635bool llvm::salvageDebugInfoForDbgValues(
1636 Instruction &I, ArrayRef<DbgVariableIntrinsic *> DbgUsers) {
1637 auto &Ctx = I.getContext();
1638 auto wrapMD = [&](Value *V) { return wrapValueInMetadata(Ctx, V); };
1639
1640 for (auto *DII : DbgUsers) {
1641 // Do not add DW_OP_stack_value for DbgDeclare and DbgAddr, because they
1642 // are implicitly pointing out the value as a DWARF memory location
1643 // description.
1644 bool StackValue = isa<DbgValueInst>(DII);
1645
1646 DIExpression *DIExpr =
1647 salvageDebugInfoImpl(I, DII->getExpression(), StackValue);
1648
1649 // salvageDebugInfoImpl should fail on examining the first element of
1650 // DbgUsers, or none of them.
1651 if (!DIExpr)
1652 return false;
1653
1654 DII->setOperand(0, wrapMD(I.getOperand(0)));
1655 DII->setOperand(2, MetadataAsValue::get(Ctx, DIExpr));
1656 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SALVAGE: " << *DII << '\n');
1657 }
1658
1659 return true;
1660}
1661
1662DIExpression *llvm::salvageDebugInfoImpl(Instruction &I,
1663 DIExpression *SrcDIExpr,
1664 bool WithStackValue) {
1665 auto &M = *I.getModule();
1666 auto &DL = M.getDataLayout();
1667
1668 // Apply a vector of opcodes to the source DIExpression.
1669 auto doSalvage = [&](SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Ops) -> DIExpression * {
1670 DIExpression *DIExpr = SrcDIExpr;
1671 if (!Ops.empty()) {
1672 DIExpr = DIExpression::prependOpcodes(DIExpr, Ops, WithStackValue);
1673 }
1674 return DIExpr;
1675 };
1676
1677 // Apply the given offset to the source DIExpression.
1678 auto applyOffset = [&](uint64_t Offset) -> DIExpression * {
1679 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Ops;
1680 DIExpression::appendOffset(Ops, Offset);
1681 return doSalvage(Ops);
1682 };
1683
1684 // initializer-list helper for applying operators to the source DIExpression.
1685 auto applyOps =
1686 [&](std::initializer_list<uint64_t> Opcodes) -> DIExpression * {
1687 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Ops(Opcodes);
1688 return doSalvage(Ops);
1689 };
1690
1691 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(&I)) {
1692 // No-op casts and zexts are irrelevant for debug info.
1693 if (CI->isNoopCast(DL) || isa<ZExtInst>(&I))
1694 return SrcDIExpr;
1695 return nullptr;
1696 } else if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(&I)) {
1697 unsigned BitWidth =
1698 M.getDataLayout().getIndexSizeInBits(GEP->getPointerAddressSpace());
1699 // Rewrite a constant GEP into a DIExpression.
1700 APInt Offset(BitWidth, 0);
1701 if (GEP->accumulateConstantOffset(M.getDataLayout(), Offset)) {
1702 return applyOffset(Offset.getSExtValue());
1703 } else {
1704 return nullptr;
1705 }
1706 } else if (auto *BI = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(&I)) {
1707 // Rewrite binary operations with constant integer operands.
1708 auto *ConstInt = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(I.getOperand(1));
1709 if (!ConstInt || ConstInt->getBitWidth() > 64)
1710 return nullptr;
1711
1712 uint64_t Val = ConstInt->getSExtValue();
1713 switch (BI->getOpcode()) {
1714 case Instruction::Add:
1715 return applyOffset(Val);
1716 case Instruction::Sub:
1717 return applyOffset(-int64_t(Val));
1718 case Instruction::Mul:
1719 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_mul});
1720 case Instruction::SDiv:
1721 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_div});
1722 case Instruction::SRem:
1723 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_mod});
1724 case Instruction::Or:
1725 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_or});
1726 case Instruction::And:
1727 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_and});
1728 case Instruction::Xor:
1729 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_xor});
1730 case Instruction::Shl:
1731 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_shl});
1732 case Instruction::LShr:
1733 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_shr});
1734 case Instruction::AShr:
1735 return applyOps({dwarf::DW_OP_constu, Val, dwarf::DW_OP_shra});
1736 default:
1737 // TODO: Salvage constants from each kind of binop we know about.
1738 return nullptr;
1739 }
1740 // *Not* to do: we should not attempt to salvage load instructions,
1741 // because the validity and lifetime of a dbg.value containing
1742 // DW_OP_deref becomes difficult to analyze. See PR40628 for examples.
1743 }
1744 return nullptr;
1745}
1746
1747/// A replacement for a dbg.value expression.
1748using DbgValReplacement = Optional<DIExpression *>;
1749
1750/// Point debug users of \p From to \p To using exprs given by \p RewriteExpr,
1751/// possibly moving/deleting users to prevent use-before-def. Returns true if
1752/// changes are made.
1753static bool rewriteDebugUsers(
1754 Instruction &From, Value &To, Instruction &DomPoint, DominatorTree &DT,
1755 function_ref<DbgValReplacement(DbgVariableIntrinsic &DII)> RewriteExpr) {
1756 // Find debug users of From.
1757 SmallVector<DbgVariableIntrinsic *, 1> Users;
1758 findDbgUsers(Users, &From);
1759 if (Users.empty())
1760 return false;
1761
1762 // Prevent use-before-def of To.
1763 bool Changed = false;
1764 SmallPtrSet<DbgVariableIntrinsic *, 1> DeleteOrSalvage;
1765 if (isa<Instruction>(&To)) {
1766 bool DomPointAfterFrom = From.getNextNonDebugInstruction() == &DomPoint;
1767
1768 for (auto *DII : Users) {
1769 // It's common to see a debug user between From and DomPoint. Move it
1770 // after DomPoint to preserve the variable update without any reordering.
1771 if (DomPointAfterFrom && DII->getNextNonDebugInstruction() == &DomPoint) {
1772 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MOVE: " << *DII << '\n');
1773 DII->moveAfter(&DomPoint);
1774 Changed = true;
1775
1776 // Users which otherwise aren't dominated by the replacement value must
1777 // be salvaged or deleted.
1778 } else if (!DT.dominates(&DomPoint, DII)) {
1779 DeleteOrSalvage.insert(DII);
1780 }
1781 }
1782 }
1783
1784 // Update debug users without use-before-def risk.
1785 for (auto *DII : Users) {
1786 if (DeleteOrSalvage.count(DII))
1787 continue;
1788
1789 LLVMContext &Ctx = DII->getContext();
1790 DbgValReplacement DVR = RewriteExpr(*DII);
1791 if (!DVR)
1792 continue;
1793
1794 DII->setOperand(0, wrapValueInMetadata(Ctx, &To));
1795 DII->setOperand(2, MetadataAsValue::get(Ctx, *DVR));
1796 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "REWRITE: " << *DII << '\n');
1797 Changed = true;
1798 }
1799
1800 if (!DeleteOrSalvage.empty()) {
1801 // Try to salvage the remaining debug users.
1802 Changed |= salvageDebugInfo(From);
1803
1804 // Delete the debug users which weren't salvaged.
1805 for (auto *DII : DeleteOrSalvage) {
1806 if (DII->getVariableLocation() == &From) {
1807 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Erased UseBeforeDef: " << *DII << '\n');
1808 DII->eraseFromParent();
1809 Changed = true;
1810 }
1811 }
1812 }
1813
1814 return Changed;
1815}
1816
1817/// Check if a bitcast between a value of type \p FromTy to type \p ToTy would
1818/// losslessly preserve the bits and semantics of the value. This predicate is
1819/// symmetric, i.e swapping \p FromTy and \p ToTy should give the same result.
1820///
1821/// Note that Type::canLosslesslyBitCastTo is not suitable here because it
1822/// allows semantically unequivalent bitcasts, such as <2 x i64> -> <4 x i32>,
1823/// and also does not allow lossless pointer <-> integer conversions.
1824static bool isBitCastSemanticsPreserving(const DataLayout &DL, Type *FromTy,
1825 Type *ToTy) {
1826 // Trivially compatible types.
1827 if (FromTy == ToTy)
1828 return true;
1829
1830 // Handle compatible pointer <-> integer conversions.
1831 if (FromTy->isIntOrPtrTy() && ToTy->isIntOrPtrTy()) {
1832 bool SameSize = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(FromTy) == DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ToTy);
1833 bool LosslessConversion = !DL.isNonIntegralPointerType(FromTy) &&
1834 !DL.isNonIntegralPointerType(ToTy);
1835 return SameSize && LosslessConversion;
1836 }
1837
1838 // TODO: This is not exhaustive.
1839 return false;
1840}
1841
1842bool llvm::replaceAllDbgUsesWith(Instruction &From, Value &To,
1843 Instruction &DomPoint, DominatorTree &DT) {
1844 // Exit early if From has no debug users.
1845 if (!From.isUsedByMetadata())
1846 return false;
1847
1848 assert(&From != &To && "Can't replace something with itself");
1849
1850 Type *FromTy = From.getType();
1851 Type *ToTy = To.getType();
1852
1853 auto Identity = [&](DbgVariableIntrinsic &DII) -> DbgValReplacement {
1854 return DII.getExpression();
1855 };
1856
1857 // Handle no-op conversions.
1858 Module &M = *From.getModule();
1859 const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
1860 if (isBitCastSemanticsPreserving(DL, FromTy, ToTy))
1861 return rewriteDebugUsers(From, To, DomPoint, DT, Identity);
1862
1863 // Handle integer-to-integer widening and narrowing.
1864 // FIXME: Use DW_OP_convert when it's available everywhere.
1865 if (FromTy->isIntegerTy() && ToTy->isIntegerTy()) {
1866 uint64_t FromBits = FromTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1867 uint64_t ToBits = ToTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1868 assert(FromBits != ToBits && "Unexpected no-op conversion");
1869
1870 // When the width of the result grows, assume that a debugger will only
1871 // access the low `FromBits` bits when inspecting the source variable.
1872 if (FromBits < ToBits)
1873 return rewriteDebugUsers(From, To, DomPoint, DT, Identity);
1874
1875 // The width of the result has shrunk. Use sign/zero extension to describe
1876 // the source variable's high bits.
1877 auto SignOrZeroExt = [&](DbgVariableIntrinsic &DII) -> DbgValReplacement {
1878 DILocalVariable *Var = DII.getVariable();
1879
1880 // Without knowing signedness, sign/zero extension isn't possible.
1881 auto Signedness = Var->getSignedness();
1882 if (!Signedness)
1883 return None;
1884
1885 bool Signed = *Signedness == DIBasicType::Signedness::Signed;
1886 dwarf::TypeKind TK = Signed ? dwarf::DW_ATE_signed : dwarf::DW_ATE_unsigned;
1887 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Ops({dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_convert, ToBits, TK,
1888 dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_convert, FromBits, TK});
1889 return DIExpression::appendToStack(DII.getExpression(), Ops);
1890 };
1891 return rewriteDebugUsers(From, To, DomPoint, DT, SignOrZeroExt);
1892 }
1893
1894 // TODO: Floating-point conversions, vectors.
1895 return false;
1896}
1897
1898unsigned llvm::removeAllNonTerminatorAndEHPadInstructions(BasicBlock *BB) {
1899 unsigned NumDeadInst = 0;
1900 // Delete the instructions backwards, as it has a reduced likelihood of
1901 // having to update as many def-use and use-def chains.
1902 Instruction *EndInst = BB->getTerminator(); // Last not to be deleted.
1903 while (EndInst != &BB->front()) {
1904 // Delete the next to last instruction.
1905 Instruction *Inst = &*--EndInst->getIterator();
1906 if (!Inst->use_empty() && !Inst->getType()->isTokenTy())
1907 Inst->replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(Inst->getType()));
1908 if (Inst->isEHPad() || Inst->getType()->isTokenTy()) {
1909 EndInst = Inst;
1910 continue;
1911 }
1912 if (!isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(Inst))
1913 ++NumDeadInst;
1914 Inst->eraseFromParent();
1915 }
1916 return NumDeadInst;
1917}
1918
1919unsigned llvm::changeToUnreachable(Instruction *I, bool UseLLVMTrap,
1920 bool PreserveLCSSA, DomTreeUpdater *DTU,
1921 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU) {
1922 BasicBlock *BB = I->getParent();
1923 std::vector <DominatorTree::UpdateType> Updates;
1924
1925 if (MSSAU)
1926 MSSAU->changeToUnreachable(I);
1927
1928 // Loop over all of the successors, removing BB's entry from any PHI
1929 // nodes.
1930 if (DTU)
1931 Updates.reserve(BB->getTerminator()->getNumSuccessors());
1932 for (BasicBlock *Successor : successors(BB)) {
1933 Successor->removePredecessor(BB, PreserveLCSSA);
1934 if (DTU)
1935 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, BB, Successor});
1936 }
1937 // Insert a call to llvm.trap right before this. This turns the undefined
1938 // behavior into a hard fail instead of falling through into random code.
1939 if (UseLLVMTrap) {
1940 Function *TrapFn =
1941 Intrinsic::getDeclaration(BB->getParent()->getParent(), Intrinsic::trap);
1942 CallInst *CallTrap = CallInst::Create(TrapFn, "", I);
1943 CallTrap->setDebugLoc(I->getDebugLoc());
1944 }
1945 auto *UI = new UnreachableInst(I->getContext(), I);
1946 UI->setDebugLoc(I->getDebugLoc());
1947
1948 // All instructions after this are dead.
1949 unsigned NumInstrsRemoved = 0;
1950 BasicBlock::iterator BBI = I->getIterator(), BBE = BB->end();
1951 while (BBI != BBE) {
1952 if (!BBI->use_empty())
1953 BBI->replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(BBI->getType()));
1954 BB->getInstList().erase(BBI++);
1955 ++NumInstrsRemoved;
1956 }
1957 if (DTU)
1958 DTU->applyUpdatesPermissive(Updates);
1959 return NumInstrsRemoved;
1960}
1961
1962/// changeToCall - Convert the specified invoke into a normal call.
1963static void changeToCall(InvokeInst *II, DomTreeUpdater *DTU = nullptr) {
1964 SmallVector<Value*, 8> Args(II->arg_begin(), II->arg_end());
1965 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
1966 II->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
1967 CallInst *NewCall = CallInst::Create(
1968 II->getFunctionType(), II->getCalledValue(), Args, OpBundles, "", II);
1969 NewCall->takeName(II);
1970 NewCall->setCallingConv(II->getCallingConv());
1971 NewCall->setAttributes(II->getAttributes());
1972 NewCall->setDebugLoc(II->getDebugLoc());
1973 NewCall->copyMetadata(*II);
1974 II->replaceAllUsesWith(NewCall);
1975
1976 // Follow the call by a branch to the normal destination.
1977 BasicBlock *NormalDestBB = II->getNormalDest();
1978 BranchInst::Create(NormalDestBB, II);
1979
1980 // Update PHI nodes in the unwind destination
1981 BasicBlock *BB = II->getParent();
1982 BasicBlock *UnwindDestBB = II->getUnwindDest();
1983 UnwindDestBB->removePredecessor(BB);
1984 II->eraseFromParent();
1985 if (DTU)
1986 DTU->applyUpdatesPermissive({{DominatorTree::Delete, BB, UnwindDestBB}});
1987}
1988
1989BasicBlock *llvm::changeToInvokeAndSplitBasicBlock(CallInst *CI,
1990 BasicBlock *UnwindEdge) {
1991 BasicBlock *BB = CI->getParent();
1992
1993 // Convert this function call into an invoke instruction. First, split the
1994 // basic block.
1995 BasicBlock *Split =
1996 BB->splitBasicBlock(CI->getIterator(), CI->getName() + ".noexc");
1997
1998 // Delete the unconditional branch inserted by splitBasicBlock
1999 BB->getInstList().pop_back();
2000
2001 // Create the new invoke instruction.
2002 SmallVector<Value *, 8> InvokeArgs(CI->arg_begin(), CI->arg_end());
2003 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
2004
2005 CI->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
2006
2007 // Note: we're round tripping operand bundles through memory here, and that
2008 // can potentially be avoided with a cleverer API design that we do not have
2009 // as of this time.
2010
2011 InvokeInst *II =
2012 InvokeInst::Create(CI->getFunctionType(), CI->getCalledValue(), Split,
2013 UnwindEdge, InvokeArgs, OpBundles, CI->getName(), BB);
2014 II->setDebugLoc(CI->getDebugLoc());
2015 II->setCallingConv(CI->getCallingConv());
2016 II->setAttributes(CI->getAttributes());
2017
2018 // Make sure that anything using the call now uses the invoke! This also
2019 // updates the CallGraph if present, because it uses a WeakTrackingVH.
2020 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(II);
2021
2022 // Delete the original call
2023 Split->getInstList().pop_front();
2024 return Split;
2025}
2026
2027static bool markAliveBlocks(Function &F,
2028 SmallPtrSetImpl<BasicBlock *> &Reachable,
2029 DomTreeUpdater *DTU = nullptr) {
2030 SmallVector<BasicBlock*, 128> Worklist;
2031 BasicBlock *BB = &F.front();
2032 Worklist.push_back(BB);
2033 Reachable.insert(BB);
2034 bool Changed = false;
2035 do {
2036 BB = Worklist.pop_back_val();
2037
2038 // Do a quick scan of the basic block, turning any obviously unreachable
2039 // instructions into LLVM unreachable insts. The instruction combining pass
2040 // canonicalizes unreachable insts into stores to null or undef.
2041 for (Instruction &I : *BB) {
2042 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I)) {
2043 Value *Callee = CI->getCalledValue();
2044 // Handle intrinsic calls.
2045 if (Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(Callee)) {
2046 auto IntrinsicID = F->getIntrinsicID();
2047 // Assumptions that are known to be false are equivalent to
2048 // unreachable. Also, if the condition is undefined, then we make the
2049 // choice most beneficial to the optimizer, and choose that to also be
2050 // unreachable.
2051 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::assume) {
2052 if (match(CI->getArgOperand(0), m_CombineOr(m_Zero(), m_Undef()))) {
2053 // Don't insert a call to llvm.trap right before the unreachable.
2054 changeToUnreachable(CI, false, false, DTU);
2055 Changed = true;
2056 break;
2057 }
2058 } else if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::experimental_guard) {
2059 // A call to the guard intrinsic bails out of the current
2060 // compilation unit if the predicate passed to it is false. If the
2061 // predicate is a constant false, then we know the guard will bail
2062 // out of the current compile unconditionally, so all code following
2063 // it is dead.
2064 //
2065 // Note: unlike in llvm.assume, it is not "obviously profitable" for
2066 // guards to treat `undef` as `false` since a guard on `undef` can
2067 // still be useful for widening.
2068 if (match(CI->getArgOperand(0), m_Zero()))
2069 if (!isa<UnreachableInst>(CI->getNextNode())) {
2070 changeToUnreachable(CI->getNextNode(), /*UseLLVMTrap=*/false,
2071 false, DTU);
2072 Changed = true;
2073 break;
2074 }
2075 }
2076 } else if ((isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Callee) &&
2077 !NullPointerIsDefined(CI->getFunction())) ||
2078 isa<UndefValue>(Callee)) {
2079 changeToUnreachable(CI, /*UseLLVMTrap=*/false, false, DTU);
2080 Changed = true;
2081 break;
2082 }
2083 if (CI->doesNotReturn() && !CI->isMustTailCall()) {
2084 // If we found a call to a no-return function, insert an unreachable
2085 // instruction after it. Make sure there isn't *already* one there
2086 // though.
2087 if (!isa<UnreachableInst>(CI->getNextNode())) {
2088 // Don't insert a call to llvm.trap right before the unreachable.
2089 changeToUnreachable(CI->getNextNode(), false, false, DTU);
2090 Changed = true;
2091 }
2092 break;
2093 }
2094 } else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
2095 // Store to undef and store to null are undefined and used to signal
2096 // that they should be changed to unreachable by passes that can't
2097 // modify the CFG.
2098
2099 // Don't touch volatile stores.
2100 if (SI->isVolatile()) continue;
2101
2102 Value *Ptr = SI->getOperand(1);
2103
2104 if (isa<UndefValue>(Ptr) ||
2105 (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Ptr) &&
2106 !NullPointerIsDefined(SI->getFunction(),
2107 SI->getPointerAddressSpace()))) {
2108 changeToUnreachable(SI, true, false, DTU);
2109 Changed = true;
2110 break;
2111 }
2112 }
2113 }
2114
2115 Instruction *Terminator = BB->getTerminator();
2116 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Terminator)) {
2117 // Turn invokes that call 'nounwind' functions into ordinary calls.
2118 Value *Callee = II->getCalledValue();
2119 if ((isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Callee) &&
2120 !NullPointerIsDefined(BB->getParent())) ||
2121 isa<UndefValue>(Callee)) {
2122 changeToUnreachable(II, true, false, DTU);
2123 Changed = true;
2124 } else if (II->doesNotThrow() && canSimplifyInvokeNoUnwind(&F)) {
2125 if (II->use_empty() && II->onlyReadsMemory()) {
2126 // jump to the normal destination branch.
2127 BasicBlock *NormalDestBB = II->getNormalDest();
2128 BasicBlock *UnwindDestBB = II->getUnwindDest();
2129 BranchInst::Create(NormalDestBB, II);
2130 UnwindDestBB->removePredecessor(II->getParent());
2131 II->eraseFromParent();
2132 if (DTU)
2133 DTU->applyUpdatesPermissive(
2134 {{DominatorTree::Delete, BB, UnwindDestBB}});
2135 } else
2136 changeToCall(II, DTU);
2137 Changed = true;
2138 }
2139 } else if (auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(Terminator)) {
2140 // Remove catchpads which cannot be reached.
2141 struct CatchPadDenseMapInfo {
2142 static CatchPadInst *getEmptyKey() {
2143 return DenseMapInfo<CatchPadInst *>::getEmptyKey();
2144 }
2145
2146 static CatchPadInst *getTombstoneKey() {
2147 return DenseMapInfo<CatchPadInst *>::getTombstoneKey();
2148 }
2149
2150 static unsigned getHashValue(CatchPadInst *CatchPad) {
2151 return static_cast<unsigned>(hash_combine_range(
2152 CatchPad->value_op_begin(), CatchPad->value_op_end()));
2153 }
2154
2155 static bool isEqual(CatchPadInst *LHS, CatchPadInst *RHS) {
2156 if (LHS == getEmptyKey() || LHS == getTombstoneKey() ||
2157 RHS == getEmptyKey() || RHS == getTombstoneKey())
2158 return LHS == RHS;
2159 return LHS->isIdenticalTo(RHS);
2160 }
2161 };
2162
2163 // Set of unique CatchPads.
2164 SmallDenseMap<CatchPadInst *, detail::DenseSetEmpty, 4,
2165 CatchPadDenseMapInfo, detail::DenseSetPair<CatchPadInst *>>
2166 HandlerSet;
2167 detail::DenseSetEmpty Empty;
2168 for (CatchSwitchInst::handler_iterator I = CatchSwitch->handler_begin(),
2169 E = CatchSwitch->handler_end();
2170 I != E; ++I) {
2171 BasicBlock *HandlerBB = *I;
2172 auto *CatchPad = cast<CatchPadInst>(HandlerBB->getFirstNonPHI());
2173 if (!HandlerSet.insert({CatchPad, Empty}).second) {
2174 CatchSwitch->removeHandler(I);
2175 --I;
2176 --E;
2177 Changed = true;
2178 }
2179 }
2180 }
2181
2182 Changed |= ConstantFoldTerminator(BB, true, nullptr, DTU);
2183 for (BasicBlock *Successor : successors(BB))
2184 if (Reachable.insert(Successor).second)
2185 Worklist.push_back(Successor);
2186 } while (!Worklist.empty());
2187 return Changed;
2188}
2189
2190void llvm::removeUnwindEdge(BasicBlock *BB, DomTreeUpdater *DTU) {
2191 Instruction *TI = BB->getTerminator();
2192
2193 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(TI)) {
2194 changeToCall(II, DTU);
2195 return;
2196 }
2197
2198 Instruction *NewTI;
2199 BasicBlock *UnwindDest;
2200
2201 if (auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(TI)) {
2202 NewTI = CleanupReturnInst::Create(CRI->getCleanupPad(), nullptr, CRI);
2203 UnwindDest = CRI->getUnwindDest();
2204 } else if (auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(TI)) {
2205 auto *NewCatchSwitch = CatchSwitchInst::Create(
2206 CatchSwitch->getParentPad(), nullptr, CatchSwitch->getNumHandlers(),
2207 CatchSwitch->getName(), CatchSwitch);
2208 for (BasicBlock *PadBB : CatchSwitch->handlers())
2209 NewCatchSwitch->addHandler(PadBB);
2210
2211 NewTI = NewCatchSwitch;
2212 UnwindDest = CatchSwitch->getUnwindDest();
2213 } else {
2214 llvm_unreachable("Could not find unwind successor");
2215 }
2216
2217 NewTI->takeName(TI);
2218 NewTI->setDebugLoc(TI->getDebugLoc());
2219 UnwindDest->removePredecessor(BB);
2220 TI->replaceAllUsesWith(NewTI);
2221 TI->eraseFromParent();
2222 if (DTU)
2223 DTU->applyUpdatesPermissive({{DominatorTree::Delete, BB, UnwindDest}});
2224}
2225
2226/// removeUnreachableBlocks - Remove blocks that are not reachable, even
2227/// if they are in a dead cycle. Return true if a change was made, false
2228/// otherwise. If `LVI` is passed, this function preserves LazyValueInfo
2229/// after modifying the CFG.
2230bool llvm::removeUnreachableBlocks(Function &F, LazyValueInfo *LVI,
2231 DomTreeUpdater *DTU,
2232 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU) {
2233 SmallPtrSet<BasicBlock*, 16> Reachable;
2234 bool Changed = markAliveBlocks(F, Reachable, DTU);
2235
2236 // If there are unreachable blocks in the CFG...
2237 if (Reachable.size() == F.size())
2238 return Changed;
2239
2240 assert(Reachable.size() < F.size());
2241 NumRemoved += F.size()-Reachable.size();
2242
2243 SmallPtrSet<BasicBlock *, 16> DeadBlockSet;
2244 for (Function::iterator I = ++F.begin(), E = F.end(); I != E; ++I) {
2245 auto *BB = &*I;
2246 if (Reachable.count(BB))
2247 continue;
2248 DeadBlockSet.insert(BB);
2249 }
2250
2251 if (MSSAU)
2252 MSSAU->removeBlocks(DeadBlockSet);
2253
2254 // Loop over all of the basic blocks that are not reachable, dropping all of
2255 // their internal references. Update DTU and LVI if available.
2256 std::vector<DominatorTree::UpdateType> Updates;
2257 for (auto *BB : DeadBlockSet) {
2258 for (BasicBlock *Successor : successors(BB)) {
2259 if (!DeadBlockSet.count(Successor))
2260 Successor->removePredecessor(BB);
2261 if (DTU)
2262 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, BB, Successor});
2263 }
2264 if (LVI)
2265 LVI->eraseBlock(BB);
2266 BB->dropAllReferences();
2267 }
2268 for (Function::iterator I = ++F.begin(); I != F.end();) {
2269 auto *BB = &*I;
2270 if (Reachable.count(BB)) {
2271 ++I;
2272 continue;
2273 }
2274 if (DTU) {
2275 // Remove the terminator of BB to clear the successor list of BB.
2276 if (BB->getTerminator())
2277 BB->getInstList().pop_back();
2278 new UnreachableInst(BB->getContext(), BB);
2279 assert(succ_empty(BB) && "The successor list of BB isn't empty before "
2280 "applying corresponding DTU updates.");
2281 ++I;
2282 } else {
2283 I = F.getBasicBlockList().erase(I);
2284 }
2285 }
2286
2287 if (DTU) {
2288 DTU->applyUpdatesPermissive(Updates);
2289 bool Deleted = false;
2290 for (auto *BB : DeadBlockSet) {
2291 if (DTU->isBBPendingDeletion(BB))
2292 --NumRemoved;
2293 else
2294 Deleted = true;
2295 DTU->deleteBB(BB);
2296 }
2297 if (!Deleted)
2298 return false;
2299 }
2300 return true;
2301}
2302
2303void llvm::combineMetadata(Instruction *K, const Instruction *J,
2304 ArrayRef<unsigned> KnownIDs, bool DoesKMove) {
2305 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 4> Metadata;
2306 K->dropUnknownNonDebugMetadata(KnownIDs);
2307 K->getAllMetadataOtherThanDebugLoc(Metadata);
2308 for (const auto &MD : Metadata) {
2309 unsigned Kind = MD.first;
2310 MDNode *JMD = J->getMetadata(Kind);
2311 MDNode *KMD = MD.second;
2312
2313 switch (Kind) {
2314 default:
2315 K->setMetadata(Kind, nullptr); // Remove unknown metadata
2316 break;
2317 case LLVMContext::MD_dbg:
2318 llvm_unreachable("getAllMetadataOtherThanDebugLoc returned a MD_dbg");
2319 case LLVMContext::MD_tbaa:
2320 K->setMetadata(Kind, MDNode::getMostGenericTBAA(JMD, KMD));
2321 break;
2322 case LLVMContext::MD_alias_scope:
2323 K->setMetadata(Kind, MDNode::getMostGenericAliasScope(JMD, KMD));
2324 break;
2325 case LLVMContext::MD_noalias:
2326 case LLVMContext::MD_mem_parallel_loop_access:
2327 K->setMetadata(Kind, MDNode::intersect(JMD, KMD));
2328 break;
2329 case LLVMContext::MD_access_group:
2330 K->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_access_group,
2331 intersectAccessGroups(K, J));
2332 break;
2333 case LLVMContext::MD_range:
2334
2335 // If K does move, use most generic range. Otherwise keep the range of
2336 // K.
2337 if (DoesKMove)
2338 // FIXME: If K does move, we should drop the range info and nonnull.
2339 // Currently this function is used with DoesKMove in passes
2340 // doing hoisting/sinking and the current behavior of using the
2341 // most generic range is correct in those cases.
2342 K->setMetadata(Kind, MDNode::getMostGenericRange(JMD, KMD));
2343 break;
2344 case LLVMContext::MD_fpmath:
2345 K->setMetadata(Kind, MDNode::getMostGenericFPMath(JMD, KMD));
2346 break;
2347 case LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load:
2348 // Only set the !invariant.load if it is present in both instructions.
2349 K->setMetadata(Kind, JMD);
2350 break;
2351 case LLVMContext::MD_nonnull:
2352 // If K does move, keep nonull if it is present in both instructions.
2353 if (DoesKMove)
2354 K->setMetadata(Kind, JMD);
2355 break;
2356 case LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group:
2357 // Preserve !invariant.group in K.
2358 break;
2359 case LLVMContext::MD_align:
2360 K->setMetadata(Kind,
2361 MDNode::getMostGenericAlignmentOrDereferenceable(JMD, KMD));
2362 break;
2363 case LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable:
2364 case LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable_or_null:
2365 K->setMetadata(Kind,
2366 MDNode::getMostGenericAlignmentOrDereferenceable(JMD, KMD));
2367 break;
2368 }
2369 }
2370 // Set !invariant.group from J if J has it. If both instructions have it
2371 // then we will just pick it from J - even when they are different.
2372 // Also make sure that K is load or store - f.e. combining bitcast with load
2373 // could produce bitcast with invariant.group metadata, which is invalid.
2374 // FIXME: we should try to preserve both invariant.group md if they are
2375 // different, but right now instruction can only have one invariant.group.
2376 if (auto *JMD = J->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group))
2377 if (isa<LoadInst>(K) || isa<StoreInst>(K))
2378 K->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group, JMD);
2379}

2381void llvm::combineMetadataForCSE(Instruction *K, const Instruction *J,
2382 bool KDominatesJ) {
2383 unsigned KnownIDs[] = {
2384 LLVMContext::MD_tbaa, LLVMContext::MD_alias_scope,
2385 LLVMContext::MD_noalias, LLVMContext::MD_range,
2386 LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load, LLVMContext::MD_nonnull,
2387 LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group, LLVMContext::MD_align,
2388 LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable,
2389 LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable_or_null,
2390 LLVMContext::MD_access_group};

2393
2394void llvm::patchReplacementInstruction(Instruction *I, Value *Repl) {
2395 auto *ReplInst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Repl);
2396 if (!ReplInst)
2397 return;
2398
2399 // Patch the replacement so that it is not more restrictive than the value
2400 // being replaced.
2401 // Note that if 'I' is a load being replaced by some operation,
2402 // for example, by an arithmetic operation, then andIRFlags()
2403 // would just erase all math flags from the original arithmetic
2404 // operation, which is clearly not wanted and not needed.
2405 if (!isa<LoadInst>(I))
2406 ReplInst->andIRFlags(I);
2407
2408 // FIXME: If both the original and replacement value are part of the
2409 // same control-flow region (meaning that the execution of one
2410 // guarantees the execution of the other), then we can combine the
2411 // noalias scopes here and do better than the general conservative
2412 // answer used in combineMetadata().
2413
2414 // In general, GVN unifies expressions over different control-flow
2415 // regions, and so we need a conservative combination of the noalias
2416 // scopes.
2417 static const unsigned KnownIDs[] = {
2418 LLVMContext::MD_tbaa, LLVMContext::MD_alias_scope,
2419 LLVMContext::MD_noalias, LLVMContext::MD_range,
2420 LLVMContext::MD_fpmath, LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load,
2421 LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group, LLVMContext::MD_nonnull,
2422 LLVMContext::MD_access_group};
2423 combineMetadata(ReplInst, I, KnownIDs, false);
2424}
2425
2426template <typename RootType, typename DominatesFn>
2427static unsigned replaceDominatedUsesWith(Value *From, Value *To,
2428 const RootType &Root,
2429 const DominatesFn &Dominates) {
2430 assert(From->getType() == To->getType());
2431
2432 unsigned Count = 0;
2433 for (Value::use_iterator UI = From->use_begin(), UE = From->use_end();
2434 UI != UE;) {
2435 Use &U = *UI++;
2436 if (!Dominates(Root, U))
2437 continue;
2438 U.set(To);
2439 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Replace dominated use of '" << From->getName()
2440 << "' as " << *To << " in " << *U << "\n");
2441 ++Count;
2442 }
2443 return Count;
2444}
2445
2446unsigned llvm::replaceNonLocalUsesWith(Instruction *From, Value *To) {
2447 assert(From->getType() == To->getType());
2448 auto *BB = From->getParent();
2449 unsigned Count = 0;
2450
2451 for (Value::use_iterator UI = From->use_begin(), UE = From->use_end();
2452 UI != UE;) {
2453 Use &U = *UI++;
2454 auto *I = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
2455 if (I->getParent() == BB)
2456 continue;
2457 U.set(To);
2458 ++Count;
2459 }
2460 return Count;
2461}

2463unsigned llvm::replaceDominatedUsesWith(Value *From, Value *To,
2464 DominatorTree &DT,
2465 const BasicBlockEdge &Root) {
2466 auto Dominates = [&DT](const BasicBlockEdge &Root, const Use &U) {
2467 return DT.dominates(Root, U);
2468 };
2469 return ::replaceDominatedUsesWith(From, To, Root, Dominates);
2470}

2472unsigned llvm::replaceDominatedUsesWith(Value *From, Value *To,
2473 DominatorTree &DT,
2474 const BasicBlock *BB) {
2475 auto ProperlyDominates = [&DT](const BasicBlock *BB, const Use &U) {
2476 auto *I = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser())->getParent();
2477 return DT.properlyDominates(BB, I);
2478 };
2479 return ::replaceDominatedUsesWith(From, To, BB, ProperlyDominates);
2480}

2482bool llvm::callsGCLeafFunction(const CallBase *Call,
2483 const TargetLibraryInfo &TLI) {
2484 // Check if the function is specifically marked as a gc leaf function.
2485 if (Call->hasFnAttr("gc-leaf-function"))
2486 return true;
2487 if (const Function *F = Call->getCalledFunction()) {
2488 if (F->hasFnAttribute("gc-leaf-function"))
2489 return true;
2490
2491 if (auto IID = F->getIntrinsicID())
2492 // Most LLVM intrinsics do not take safepoints.
2493 return IID != Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint &&
2494 IID != Intrinsic::experimental_deoptimize;
2495 }
2496
2497 // Lib calls can be materialized by some passes, and won't be
2498 // marked as 'gc-leaf-function.' All available Libcalls are
2499 // GC-leaf.
2500 LibFunc LF;
2501 if (TLI.getLibFunc(ImmutableCallSite(Call), LF)) {
2502 return TLI.has(LF);
2503 }
2504
2505 return false;
2506}

2508void llvm::copyNonnullMetadata(const LoadInst &OldLI, MDNode *N,
2509 LoadInst &NewLI) {
2510 auto *NewTy = NewLI.getType();
2511
2512 // This only directly applies if the new type is also a pointer.
2513 if (NewTy->isPointerTy()) {
2514 NewLI.setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_nonnull, N);
2515 return;
2516 }
2517
2518 // The only other translation we can do is to integral loads with !range
2519 // metadata.
2520 if (!NewTy->isIntegerTy())
2521 return;
2522
2523 MDBuilder MDB(NewLI.getContext());
2524 const Value *Ptr = OldLI.getPointerOperand();
2525 auto *ITy = cast<IntegerType>(NewTy);
2526 auto *NullInt = ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(
2527 ConstantPointerNull::get(cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())), ITy);
2528 auto *NonNullInt = ConstantExpr::getAdd(NullInt, ConstantInt::get(ITy, 1));
2529 NewLI.setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range,
2530 MDB.createRange(NonNullInt, NullInt));
2531}
2532
2533void llvm::copyRangeMetadata(const DataLayout &DL, const LoadInst &OldLI,
2534 MDNode *N, LoadInst &NewLI) {
2535 auto *NewTy = NewLI.getType();
2536
2537 // Give up unless it is converted to a pointer where there is a single very
2538 // valuable mapping we can do reliably.
2539 // FIXME: It would be nice to propagate this in more ways, but the type
2540 // conversions make it hard.
2541 if (!NewTy->isPointerTy())
2542 return;
2543
2544 unsigned BitWidth = DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(NewTy);
2545 if (!getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*N).contains(APInt(BitWidth, 0))) {
2546 MDNode *NN = MDNode::get(OldLI.getContext(), None);
2547 NewLI.setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_nonnull, NN);
2548 }
2549}

2551void llvm::dropDebugUsers(Instruction &I) {
2552 SmallVector<DbgVariableIntrinsic *, 1> DbgUsers;
2553 findDbgUsers(DbgUsers, &I);
2554 for (auto *DII : DbgUsers)
2555 DII->eraseFromParent();
2556}
2557
2558void llvm::hoistAllInstructionsInto(BasicBlock *DomBlock, Instruction *InsertPt,
2559 BasicBlock *BB) {
2560 // Since we are moving the instructions out of its basic block, we do not
2561 // retain their original debug locations (DILocations) and debug intrinsic
2562 // instructions.
2563 //
2564 // Doing so would degrade the debugging experience and adversely affect the
2565 // accuracy of profiling information.
2566 //
2567 // Currently, when hoisting the instructions, we take the following actions:
2568 // - Remove their debug intrinsic instructions.
2569 // - Set their debug locations to the values from the insertion point.
2570 //
2571 // As per PR39141 (comment #8), the more fundamental reason why the dbg.values
2572 // need to be deleted, is because there will not be any instructions with a
2573 // DILocation in either branch left after performing the transformation. We
2574 // can only insert a dbg.value after the two branches are joined again.
2575 //
2576 // See PR38762, PR39243 for more details.
2577 //
2578 // TODO: Extend llvm.dbg.value to take more than one SSA Value (PR39141) to
2579 // encode predicated DIExpressions that yield different results on different
2580 // code paths.
2581 for (BasicBlock::iterator II = BB->begin(), IE = BB->end(); II != IE;) {
2582 Instruction *I = &*II;
2583 I->dropUnknownNonDebugMetadata();
2584 if (I->isUsedByMetadata())
2585 dropDebugUsers(*I);
2586 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I)) {
2587 // Remove DbgInfo Intrinsics.
2588 II = I->eraseFromParent();
2589 continue;
2590 }
2591 I->setDebugLoc(InsertPt->getDebugLoc());
2592 ++II;
2593 }
2594 DomBlock->getInstList().splice(InsertPt->getIterator(), BB->getInstList(),
2595 BB->begin(),
2596 BB->getTerminator()->getIterator());
2597}

2599namespace {

2601/// A potential constituent of a bitreverse or bswap expression. See
2602/// collectBitParts for a fuller explanation.
2603struct BitPart {
2604 BitPart(Value *P, unsigned BW) : Provider(P) {
2605 Provenance.resize(BW);
2606 }
2607
2608 /// The Value that this is a bitreverse/bswap of.
2609 Value *Provider;
2610
2611 /// The "provenance" of each bit. Provenance[A] = B means that bit A
2612 /// in Provider becomes bit B in the result of this expression.
2613 SmallVector<int8_t, 32> Provenance; // int8_t means max size is i128.
2614
2615 enum { Unset = -1 };
2616};
2617
2618} // end anonymous namespace
2619
2620/// Analyze the specified subexpression and see if it is capable of providing
2621/// pieces of a bswap or bitreverse. The subexpression provides a potential
2622/// piece of a bswap or bitreverse if it can be proven that each non-zero bit in
2623/// the output of the expression came from a corresponding bit in some other
2624/// value. This function is recursive, and the end result is a mapping of
2625/// bitnumber to bitnumber. It is the caller's responsibility to validate that
2626/// the bitnumber to bitnumber mapping is correct for a bswap or bitreverse.
2627///
2628/// For example, if the current subexpression if "(shl i32 %X, 24)" then we know
2629/// that the expression deposits the low byte of %X into the high byte of the
2630/// result and that all other bits are zero. This expression is accepted and a
2631/// BitPart is returned with Provider set to %X and Provenance[24-31] set to
2632/// [0-7].
2633///
2634/// To avoid revisiting values, the BitPart results are memoized into the
2635/// provided map. To avoid unnecessary copying of BitParts, BitParts are
2636/// constructed in-place in the \c BPS map. Because of this \c BPS needs to
2637/// store BitParts objects, not pointers. As we need the concept of a nullptr
2638/// BitParts (Value has been analyzed and the analysis failed), we an Optional
2639/// type instead to provide the same functionality.
2640///
2641/// Because we pass around references into \c BPS, we must use a container that
2642/// does not invalidate internal references (std::map instead of DenseMap).
2643static const Optional<BitPart> &
2644collectBitParts(Value *V, bool MatchBSwaps, bool MatchBitReversals,
2645 std::map<Value *, Optional<BitPart>> &BPS, int Depth) {
2646 auto I = BPS.find(V);
2647 if (I != BPS.end())
2648 return I->second;
2649
2650 auto &Result = BPS[V] = None;
2651 auto BitWidth = cast<IntegerType>(V->getType())->getBitWidth();
2652
2653 // Prevent stack overflow by limiting the recursion depth
2654 if (Depth == BitPartRecursionMaxDepth) {
2655 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "collectBitParts max recursion depth reached.\n");
2656 return Result;
2657 }
2658
2659 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
2660 // If this is an or instruction, it may be an inner node of the bswap.
2661 if (I->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or) {
2662 auto &A = collectBitParts(I->getOperand(0), MatchBSwaps,
2663 MatchBitReversals, BPS, Depth + 1);
2664 auto &B = collectBitParts(I->getOperand(1), MatchBSwaps,
2665 MatchBitReversals, BPS, Depth + 1);
2666 if (!A || !B)
2667 return Result;
2668
2669 // Try and merge the two together.
2670 if (!A->Provider || A->Provider != B->Provider)
2671 return Result;
2672
2673 Result = BitPart(A->Provider, BitWidth);
2674 for (unsigned i = 0; i < A->Provenance.size(); ++i) {
2675 if (A->Provenance[i] != BitPart::Unset &&
2676 B->Provenance[i] != BitPart::Unset &&
2677 A->Provenance[i] != B->Provenance[i])
2678 return Result = None;
2679
2680 if (A->Provenance[i] == BitPart::Unset)
2681 Result->Provenance[i] = B->Provenance[i];
2682 else
2683 Result->Provenance[i] = A->Provenance[i];
2684 }
2685
2686 return Result;
2687 }
2688
2689 // If this is a logical shift by a constant, recurse then shift the result.
2690 if (I->isLogicalShift() && isa<ConstantInt>(I->getOperand(1))) {
2691 unsigned BitShift =
2692 cast<ConstantInt>(I->getOperand(1))->getLimitedValue(~0U);
2693 // Ensure the shift amount is defined.
2694 if (BitShift > BitWidth)
2695 return Result;
2696
2697 auto &Res = collectBitParts(I->getOperand(0), MatchBSwaps,
2698 MatchBitReversals, BPS, Depth + 1);
2699 if (!Res)
2700 return Result;
2701 Result = Res;
2702
2703 // Perform the "shift" on BitProvenance.
2704 auto &P = Result->Provenance;
2705 if (I->getOpcode() == Instruction::Shl) {
2706 P.erase(std::prev(P.end(), BitShift), P.end());
2707 P.insert(P.begin(), BitShift, BitPart::Unset);
2708 } else {
2709 P.erase(P.begin(), std::next(P.begin(), BitShift));
2710 P.insert(P.end(), BitShift, BitPart::Unset);
2711 }
2712
2713 return Result;
2714 }
2715
2716 // If this is a logical 'and' with a mask that clears bits, recurse then
2717 // unset the appropriate bits.
2718 if (I->getOpcode() == Instruction::And &&
2719 isa<ConstantInt>(I->getOperand(1))) {
2720 APInt Bit(I->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(), 1);
2721 const APInt &AndMask = cast<ConstantInt>(I->getOperand(1))->getValue();
2722
2723 // Check that the mask allows a multiple of 8 bits for a bswap, for an
2724 // early exit.
2725 unsigned NumMaskedBits = AndMask.countPopulation();
2726 if (!MatchBitReversals && NumMaskedBits % 8 != 0)
2727 return Result;
2728
2729 auto &Res = collectBitParts(I->getOperand(0), MatchBSwaps,
2730 MatchBitReversals, BPS, Depth + 1);
2731 if (!Res)
2732 return Result;
2733 Result = Res;
2734
2735 for (unsigned i = 0; i < BitWidth; ++i, Bit <<= 1)
2736 // If the AndMask is zero for this bit, clear the bit.
2737 if ((AndMask & Bit) == 0)
2738 Result->Provenance[i] = BitPart::Unset;
2739 return Result;
2740 }
2741
2742 // If this is a zext instruction zero extend the result.
2743 if (I->getOpcode() == Instruction::ZExt) {
2744 auto &Res = collectBitParts(I->getOperand(0), MatchBSwaps,
2745 MatchBitReversals, BPS, Depth + 1);
2746 if (!Res)
2747 return Result;
2748
2749 Result = BitPart(Res->Provider, BitWidth);
2750 auto NarrowBitWidth =
2751 cast<IntegerType>(cast<ZExtInst>(I)->getSrcTy())->getBitWidth();
2752 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NarrowBitWidth; ++i)
2753 Result->Provenance[i] = Res->Provenance[i];
2754 for (unsigned i = NarrowBitWidth; i < BitWidth; ++i)
2755 Result->Provenance[i] = BitPart::Unset;
2756 return Result;
2757 }
2758 }
2759
2760 // Okay, we got to something that isn't a shift, 'or' or 'and'. This must be
2761 // the input value to the bswap/bitreverse.
2762 Result = BitPart(V, BitWidth);
2763 for (unsigned i = 0; i < BitWidth; ++i)
2764 Result->Provenance[i] = i;
2765 return Result;
2766}
2767
2768static bool bitTransformIsCorrectForBSwap(unsigned From, unsigned To,
2769 unsigned BitWidth) {
2770 if (From % 8 != To % 8)
2771 return false;
2772 // Convert from bit indices to byte indices and check for a byte reversal.
2773 From >>= 3;
2774 To >>= 3;
2775 BitWidth >>= 3;
2776 return From == BitWidth - To - 1;
2777}
2778
2779static bool bitTransformIsCorrectForBitReverse(unsigned From, unsigned To,
2780 unsigned BitWidth) {
2781 return From == BitWidth - To - 1;
2782}
2783
2784bool llvm::recognizeBSwapOrBitReverseIdiom(
2785 Instruction *I, bool MatchBSwaps, bool MatchBitReversals,
2786 SmallVectorImpl<Instruction *> &InsertedInsts) {
2787 if (Operator::getOpcode(I) != Instruction::Or)
2788 return false;
2789 if (!MatchBSwaps && !MatchBitReversals)
2790 return false;
2791 IntegerType *ITy = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(I->getType());
2792 if (!ITy || ITy->getBitWidth() > 128)
2793 return false; // Can't do vectors or integers > 128 bits.
2794 unsigned BW = ITy->getBitWidth();
2795
2796 unsigned DemandedBW = BW;
2797 IntegerType *DemandedTy = ITy;
2798 if (I->hasOneUse()) {
2799 if (TruncInst *Trunc = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(I->user_back())) {
2800 DemandedTy = cast<IntegerType>(Trunc->getType());
2801 DemandedBW = DemandedTy->getBitWidth();
2802 }
2803 }
2804
2805 // Try to find all the pieces corresponding to the bswap.
2806 std::map<Value *, Optional<BitPart>> BPS;
2807 auto Res = collectBitParts(I, MatchBSwaps, MatchBitReversals, BPS, 0);
2808 if (!Res)
2809 return false;
2810 auto &BitProvenance = Res->Provenance;
2811
2812 // Now, is the bit permutation correct for a bswap or a bitreverse? We can
2813 // only byteswap values with an even number of bytes.
2814 bool OKForBSwap = DemandedBW % 16 == 0, OKForBitReverse = true;
2815 for (unsigned i = 0; i < DemandedBW; ++i) {
2816 OKForBSwap &=
2817 bitTransformIsCorrectForBSwap(BitProvenance[i], i, DemandedBW);
2818 OKForBitReverse &=
2819 bitTransformIsCorrectForBitReverse(BitProvenance[i], i, DemandedBW);
2820 }
2821
2822 Intrinsic::ID Intrin;
2823 if (OKForBSwap && MatchBSwaps)
2824 Intrin = Intrinsic::bswap;
2825 else if (OKForBitReverse && MatchBitReversals)
2826 Intrin = Intrinsic::bitreverse;
2827 else
2828 return false;
2829
2830 if (ITy != DemandedTy) {
2831 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(I->getModule(), Intrin, DemandedTy);
2832 Value *Provider = Res->Provider;
2833 IntegerType *ProviderTy = cast<IntegerType>(Provider->getType());
2834 // We may need to truncate the provider.
2835 if (DemandedTy != ProviderTy) {
2836 auto *Trunc = CastInst::Create(Instruction::Trunc, Provider, DemandedTy,
2837 "trunc", I);
2838 InsertedInsts.push_back(Trunc);
2839 Provider = Trunc;
2840 }
2841 auto *CI = CallInst::Create(F, Provider, "rev", I);
2842 InsertedInsts.push_back(CI);
2843 auto *ExtInst = CastInst::Create(Instruction::ZExt, CI, ITy, "zext", I);
2844 InsertedInsts.push_back(ExtInst);
2845 return true;
2846 }
2847
2848 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(I->getModule(), Intrin, ITy);
2849 InsertedInsts.push_back(CallInst::Create(F, Res->Provider, "rev", I));
2850 return true;
2851}

2853// CodeGen has special handling for some string functions that may replace
2854// them with target-specific intrinsics. Since that'd skip our interceptors
2855// in ASan/MSan/TSan/DFSan, and thus make us miss some memory accesses,
2856// we mark affected calls as NoBuiltin, which will disable optimization
2857// in CodeGen.
2858void llvm::maybeMarkSanitizerLibraryCallNoBuiltin(
2859 CallInst *CI, const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
2860 Function *F = CI->getCalledFunction();
2861 LibFunc Func;
2862 if (F && !F->hasLocalLinkage() && F->hasName() &&
2863 TLI->getLibFunc(F->getName(), Func) && TLI->hasOptimizedCodeGen(Func) &&
2864 !F->doesNotAccessMemory())
2865 CI->addAttribute(AttributeList::FunctionIndex, Attribute::NoBuiltin);
2866}

2868bool llvm::canReplaceOperandWithVariable(const Instruction *I, unsigned OpIdx) {
2869 // We can't have a PHI with a metadata type.
2870 if (I->getOperand(OpIdx)->getType()->isMetadataTy())
2871 return false;
2872
2873 // Early exit.
2874 if (!isa<Constant>(I->getOperand(OpIdx)))
2875 return true;
2876
2877 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
2878 default:
2879 return true;
2880 case Instruction::Call:
2881 case Instruction::Invoke:
2882 // Can't handle inline asm. Skip it.
2883 if (isa<InlineAsm>(ImmutableCallSite(I).getCalledValue()))
2884 return false;
2885 // Many arithmetic intrinsics have no issue taking a
2886 // variable, however it's hard to distingish these from
2887 // specials such as @llvm.frameaddress that require a constant.
2888 if (isa<IntrinsicInst>(I))
2889 return false;
2890
2891 // Constant bundle operands may need to retain their constant-ness for
2892 // correctness.
2893 if (ImmutableCallSite(I).isBundleOperand(OpIdx))
2894 return false;
2895 return true;
2896 case Instruction::ShuffleVector:
2897 // Shufflevector masks are constant.
2898 return OpIdx != 2;
2899 case Instruction::Switch:
2900 case Instruction::ExtractValue:
2901 // All operands apart from the first are constant.
2902 return OpIdx == 0;
2903 case Instruction::InsertValue:
2904 // All operands apart from the first and the second are constant.
2905 return OpIdx < 2;
2906 case Instruction::Alloca:
2907 // Static allocas (constant size in the entry block) are handled by
2908 // prologue/epilogue insertion so they're free anyway. We definitely don't
2909 // want to make them non-constant.
2910 return !cast<AllocaInst>(I)->isStaticAlloca();
2911 case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
2912 if (OpIdx == 0)
2913 return true;
2914 gep_type_iterator It = gep_type_begin(I);
2915 for (auto E = std::next(It, OpIdx); It != E; ++It)
2916 if (It.isStruct())
2917 return false;
2918 return true;
2919 }
2920}

2922using AllocaForValueMapTy = DenseMap<Value *, AllocaInst *>;
2923AllocaInst *llvm::findAllocaForValue(Value *V,
2924 AllocaForValueMapTy &AllocaForValue) {
2925 if (AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(V))
2926 return AI;
2927 // See if we've already calculated (or started to calculate) alloca for a
2928 // given value.
2929 AllocaForValueMapTy::iterator I = AllocaForValue.find(V);
2930 if (I != AllocaForValue.end())
2931 return I->second;
2932 // Store 0 while we're calculating alloca for value V to avoid
2933 // infinite recursion if the value references itself.
2934 AllocaForValue[V] = nullptr;
2935 AllocaInst *Res = nullptr;
2936 if (CastInst *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V))
2937 Res = findAllocaForValue(CI->getOperand(0), AllocaForValue);
2938 else if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(V)) {
2939 for (Value *IncValue : PN->incoming_values()) {
2940 // Allow self-referencing phi-nodes.
2941 if (IncValue == PN)
2942 continue;
2943 AllocaInst *IncValueAI = findAllocaForValue(IncValue, AllocaForValue);
2944 // AI for incoming values should exist and should all be equal.
2945 if (IncValueAI == nullptr || (Res != nullptr && IncValueAI != Res))
2946 return nullptr;
2947 Res = IncValueAI;
2948 }
2949 } else if (GetElementPtrInst *EP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(V)) {
2950 Res = findAllocaForValue(EP->getPointerOperand(), AllocaForValue);
2951 } else {
2952 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Alloca search cancelled on unknown instruction: "
2953 << *V << "\n");
2954 }
2955 if (Res)
2956 AllocaForValue[V] = Res;
2957 return Res;
2958}
